1
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:17,433
Let's see if you still
don't learn your lesson.

2
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:19,167
Let's report it to the police.

3
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,367
Wait, wait.

4
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:24,500
We're still not sure
if your employer is hurting her.

5
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:27,267
Your foot will get amputated
if it gets worse.

6
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:30,067
Please tell me you won't
do that. Mommy, please.

7
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:32,633
You can treat me as your mom.

8
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:33,867
And I'm willing to carry

9
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,967
whatever your burdens are
right now.

10
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:40,967
If you feel dark around you,
look at the sky.

11
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:44,400
You'll find at least
one star shining.

12
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:46,133
You'll realize there's light.

13
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:51,967
This wouldn't have happened if
you had followed what I said.

14
00:00:52,033 --> 00:00:53,233
You're burning.

15
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:55,900
I'll call your mom. Stay here.

16
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:32,367
You can get the head.
Contribution.

17
00:01:32,433 --> 00:01:34,033
But my second one...

18
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,333
flushes.

19
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:37,833
And lastly, royal flush.

20
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,100
- Nice!
- See?

21
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:40,600
How? How did you win?

22
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,267
- Please explain it to us.
- How? You're acting crazy.

23
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:43,333
Look.

24
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:47,167
I have an ace, king, and queen.

25
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,600
Like Queen Olive.

26
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:50,633
Queen. Acting like a queen.

27
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:53,967
And then I have a jack,
10, all cards are diamonds.

28
00:01:54,033 --> 00:01:55,367
Royal flush.

29
00:01:55,433 --> 00:02:00,300
But I don't see Olive's
daughter go out.

30
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:02,867
Even in the garden.

31
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:05,367
Aren't you friends with Flor?

32
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:07,233
- She doesn't share stories?
- Place your bets.

33
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,367
Don't you know anything
about Olive?

34
00:02:09,433 --> 00:02:12,800
Oh no, Flor doesn't tell me
anything.

35
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:14,200
She's scared.

36
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:17,000
She doesn't want to get fired.

37
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:18,533
Wait.

38
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,700
Isn't your daughter working
for them as a laundress?

39
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:24,500
What does she tell you?

40
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:25,900
She doesn't know anything.

41
00:02:25,967 --> 00:02:27,833
She doesn't meddle.

42
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,900
She only does her job.

43
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:35,600
- Here you go.
- I will win this time.

44
00:02:35,667 --> 00:02:38,567
Give me some good cards.
Did you wash your hands?

45
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:41,133
- You're unbelievable.
- Give us some luck.

46
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,233
- Wiro!
- Hey.

47
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:45,000
Don't you have a tricycle?

48
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:47,467
Someone borrowed it
earlier, Flor.

49
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:48,900
Can you call him?

50
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:51,033
I'll rent it. I just need
to buy a medicine.

51
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,033
Please.
Hurry.

52
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,733
Why? What happened?

53
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,833
Hey, Emma.

54
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,000
Mom?

55
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:14,400
I saw Flor.

56
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:16,300
She was going to buy medicine.

57
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,400
What really is the illness
of your employer's daughter?

58
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:19,800
The kid named Mookie?

59
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:22,067
I heard she has a high fever.

60
00:03:22,167 --> 00:03:24,400
What?

61
00:03:24,467 --> 00:03:25,433
Hey.

62
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,400
Are you okay?

63
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,167
Yes, Mom.

64
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:35,467
Mom, can I go out real quick?

65
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:36,633
I'll be right back.

66
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,267
Can you take care of cooking?

67
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,433
What? Where are you going?

68
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,433
- I'll be right back.
- It's already dark.

69
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,667
- The rain is heavy.
- I'll be right back.

70
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:49,500
- Be safe.
- I will!

71
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:30,867
Mookie?

72
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,667
Mommy...

73
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:24,867
Mookie?

74
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:28,067
Mookie.

75
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,433
Mookie.

76
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:35,433
Mookie, are you okay?

77
00:05:35,533 --> 00:05:37,533
Mookie, do you still
have a fever?

78
00:05:38,567 --> 00:05:39,767
Mookie.

79
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:05,233
Mookie!

80
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,833
Mookie! Mookie!

81
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:12,667
Mookie! Mookie!

82
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:18,967
Mookie!

83
00:06:20,233 --> 00:06:21,967
Mookie!

84
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:23,700
Mookie!

85
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,633
My child!

86
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,800
Dear!

87
00:06:39,867 --> 00:06:41,467
Mookie?

88
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:47,133
Mookie...

89
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:53,333
Mookie...

90
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,933
Mookie!

91
00:07:11,100 --> 00:07:12,300
Emma...

92
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,600
What?

93
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:31,300
You can't send a mechanic?

94
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:35,033
I paid you a lot, but you
didn't do your job well!

95
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:40,033
Where is Emma going?

96
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:42,733
Emma, what are you doing?

97
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:54,867
Ma'am Olive?

98
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:59,633
It's you, Ma'am!

99
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:02,567
Oh, dear.

100
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,300
It's amazing, isn't it?

101
00:08:04,367 --> 00:08:05,900
Fate is really something.

102
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:08,200
It always brings us together.

103
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:11,000
Oh, Ma'am!

104
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:16,367
Maybe we were close
in our past lives.

105
00:08:17,933 --> 00:08:19,167
What do you think, Ma'am?

106
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:23,933
What are you doing here?

107
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,533
Isn't it obvious?

108
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,867
It broke down.

109
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:33,200
What is? Your stomach?

110
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:34,067
LBM?

111
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:36,167
Ma'am, come on! I live nearby.

112
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:38,133
I have a restroom and medicines!
Come on! Let's go!

113
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,100
Ma'am!

114
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,600
My car broke down.

115
00:08:42,667 --> 00:08:44,167
Oh, this.

116
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:47,500
Unbelievable! You have a very
nice car, but it's not working?

117
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:49,200
Ma'am!

118
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:51,700
Someone who's playing cards
with me

119
00:08:51,767 --> 00:08:53,400
isn't just a good gambler.

120
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:54,700
He's also a good mechanic.

121
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:59,000
And he has a tricycle.

122
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,033
Does my car look like
a tricycle?

123
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:04,733
Definitely not.

124
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:08,167
I don't just let anyone
touch my car.

125
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:11,167
It might get even worse.

126
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:15,900
Madam, he works at a repair shop
as his side hustle.

127
00:09:15,967 --> 00:09:17,467
Come on.

128
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:20,633
He's good. I can vouch for him.

129
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,900
I'll call him.

130
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,667
Hold on.

131
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:31,000
Hello.

132
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:32,533
Wiro.

133
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,100
Don't go out tonight.

134
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,900
We have a side hustle.

135
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:38,167
It's just near my house.

136
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:40,433
Come on! Hurry up!

137
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,800
Okay.

138
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:45,900
Ma'am!

139
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:50,200
He's on his way.

140
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,400
Come on.

141
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:05,400
Emma?

142
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:07,167
Emma...

143
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,867
am I just dreaming?

144
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:11,633
What?

145
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:15,767
Did God already answer
my prayer...

146
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,867
to see you?

147
00:10:22,933 --> 00:10:24,300
Mookie.

148
00:10:24,367 --> 00:10:26,100
Is it really you,

149
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,467
Emma?

150
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,100
Mookie, it's me.

151
00:10:32,233 --> 00:10:33,333
It's me.

152
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,533
It's me.

153
00:10:36,633 --> 00:10:38,400
I'm real.

154
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,300
I'm Emma.

155
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,233
You know...

156
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:48,233
I was calling you earlier.

157
00:10:50,133 --> 00:10:54,567
He listened to me.

158
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,133
Emma...

159
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:01,267
thank you.

160
00:11:03,933 --> 00:11:05,500
Thank you.

161
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:07,000
Thank you.

162
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,200
Mookie?

163
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,167
Mookie!

164
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:18,033
Mookie!

165
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:19,767
Mookie!

166
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:20,833
My God!

167
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:24,567
Mookie!

168
00:12:35,967 --> 00:12:36,967
Go, Madam.

169
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:38,333
Start the car!

170
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,033
See?

171
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,867
He's good!

172
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:46,533
I told you, Madam.

173
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,667
My friend, Wiro, is great.

174
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:50,533
He doesn't just go out for fun.

175
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:53,067
He really is great!

176
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:54,800
Right, Madam?

177
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:58,133
So, Madam,
what's your plan now?

178
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,933
I did my job well.

179
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,233
Impress us a little.

180
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:07,733
What happened?

181
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,967
Unbelievable.
She didn't even thank us.

182
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:11,867
She's not just grumpy.
She's also stingy.

183
00:13:11,933 --> 00:13:13,800
- Hey. What's that?
- Hey.

184
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,133
Madam?

185
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,367
Is this for us?

186
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,600
You're so kind, Madam.

187
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:26,233
- I told you, she's kind.
- Thank you!

188
00:13:26,300 --> 00:13:27,567
Really!

189
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:29,233
Madam!

190
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:31,067
I hope you get even more lucky!

191
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:32,367
I hope you get
even more wealthy!

192
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:34,800
Yes, super!

193
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:37,333
Hey.

194
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,833
We can now have fun!

195
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,633
- Crazy.
- What?

196
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:45,967
She's generous.

197
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,533
Right?

198
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:50,400
We can now drink.

199
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:51,500
Crazy.

200
00:13:51,567 --> 00:13:52,633
- I have a debt to pay.
- I'm already thirsty.

201
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,933
I have to pay for our rent.

202
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,033
If only I were your mother,

203
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:14,233
I would never neglect you.

204
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:24,200
It's okay.

205
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:29,033
You can call me daughter.

206
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,067
But...

207
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:38,667
can I call you mom?

208
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:41,933
But...

209
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,967
your mom will get mad.

210
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:46,000
Don't worry.

211
00:14:46,067 --> 00:14:48,833
I won't tell her.

212
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,833
Honestly,

213
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:57,833
you made me feel like
someone was taking care of me.

214
00:14:57,900 --> 00:15:01,000
So it feels really good.

215
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:03,933
I want you to be my mother.

216
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:07,900
I feel like...

217
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,367
it's like...

218
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,200
you're my mother.

219
00:15:14,433 --> 00:15:15,433
Yes.

220
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:19,200
You can call me mom.

221
00:15:19,267 --> 00:15:20,367
Really?

222
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:23,667
That's okay with me.

223
00:15:24,767 --> 00:15:27,167
You can call me
whatever you want.

224
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,300
What matters is you get better.

225
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:38,033
Thank you...

226
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:40,733
Mommy Emma.

227
00:16:03,467 --> 00:16:04,600
My mommy.

228
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:07,100
Mommy Emma,

229
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,633
even if I don't write this
in my diary,

230
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:15,333
I will never forget this night.

231
00:16:20,567 --> 00:16:21,933
Me, too.

232
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:26,267
I might not be able to sleep
when I get home.

233
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:28,233
Because I'm thinking about you.

234
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,933
I lost my baby

235
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,967
without even letting her
feel my care and love.

236
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:39,867
But you know,

237
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:42,233
believe it or not,

238
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:45,433
the longing I feel for my child
is slowly going away.

239
00:16:46,067 --> 00:16:48,167
Because you fill it.

240
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:55,400
You just don't know how much
you make me happy, Mookie.

241
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:57,500
Dear, thank you.

242
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,233
Emma!

243
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,967
What are you doing here?

244
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:15,000
Who said you can go up here
during off-hours?

245
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:17,300
Flor, please hear me out.

246
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:18,633
What's wrong with you, Emma?

247
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:23,067
Don't you know what will happen
to you if Ma'am Olive sees you?

248
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:24,133
I will get in trouble, too!

249
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,800
We'll all get in trouble!

250
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:26,500
Leave!

251
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,133
Go, get out!

252
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,167
Mom.

253
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:29,900
Mookie!

254
00:17:29,967 --> 00:17:31,033
Mom.

255
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,300
Mom, please, don't leave me.

256
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,100
Come on!

257
00:17:35,167 --> 00:17:37,733
- Your mom might see me, Mookie.
- Mom, please.

258
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,433
I don't want
to be alone here again.

259
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:41,267
- Mom, please.
- That's enough.

260
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,633
Mookie, stop! Get out!

261
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:43,900
Our employer
will be here any minute!

262
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:45,600
Mookie, that's enough! Hey!

263
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:47,400
- I'll get in trouble!
- Mom!

264
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:49,800
You're way out of line!

265
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,033
Get out!

266
00:18:03,167 --> 00:18:05,633
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry?

267
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:09,300
You didn't even tell me
you were coming.

268
00:18:09,367 --> 00:18:12,167
I heard from my mom
that Mookie was sick.

269
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:13,333
And you went out
to buy medicines.

270
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:15,533
I felt bad for the kid
because she had no one with her.

271
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,300
No!

272
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:19,500
Ma'am Olive must know
about this!

273
00:18:19,567 --> 00:18:22,600
I will tell her to fire you.

274
00:18:22,700 --> 00:18:24,033
Come on!

275
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:25,000
- Flor.
- What?

276
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:27,467
You can't tell
Ma'am Olive what I did.

277
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:28,600
Why?

278
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:30,567
You'll get blamed, too.

279
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:33,167
You left the gate open.
That's why I was able to get in.

280
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:35,900
You might lose your job, too.

281
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:41,867
You told me you're supporting
your family.

282
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:43,800
What if you lose your job?

283
00:18:58,067 --> 00:18:59,900
Isn't that Emma?

284
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:01,567
Ems!

285
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,867
Ems! Ems!

286
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:04,867
Dan!

287
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:06,467
What are you doing here?

288
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,967
This is my route going home.

289
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:09,933
How about you?
Did you work overtime?

290
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,100
No.

291
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:12,233
Then what are you doing here?

292
00:19:20,967 --> 00:19:22,467
Can I just explain it at home?

293
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,800
Okay, okay. Come on.

294
00:19:23,867 --> 00:19:24,967
Get in.

295
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,733
Be careful.

296
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:53,700
Mookie doesn't have a fever.

297
00:19:53,767 --> 00:19:55,233
Yes, Ma'am.

298
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,833
I've given her medicine.

299
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,967
I went out to buy it.

300
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:03,067
You went out?

301
00:20:03,167 --> 00:20:06,300
You left Mookie alone
in the house?

302
00:20:09,533 --> 00:20:13,667
What if someone else got in
and took Mookie?

303
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:15,967
Didn't you think about that?

304
00:20:16,033 --> 00:20:18,367
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

305
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:20,833
I can't lose Mookie.

306
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:32,100
That can't happen!

307
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,400
I won't let that happen!

308
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,200
No!

309
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:58,033
What if someone got in
and took Mookie?

310
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:12,867
Mookie?

311
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,600
Mookie?

312
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:25,533
Mookie, dear?

313
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,167
Mookie.

314
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,233
Mookie...

315
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:39,367
I thought...

316
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:44,067
Let go of me.
I don't want you anymore.

317
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:46,600
Haven't you been torturing me
for so long?

318
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:49,233
That's why you should be alone.

319
00:21:50,767 --> 00:21:53,767
You should be left alone.

320
00:21:58,267 --> 00:22:00,767
I am so fond of Mookie.

321
00:22:00,833 --> 00:22:01,967
It was my first time seeing her,

322
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:04,633
but it felt like we've known
each other for a long time.

323
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:07,633
I think your leg
needs to be amputated

324
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:10,833
to prevent the infection
from spreading any further.

325
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:13,400
No, Mommy.
There has to be another way.

326
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:15,333
Emma, why is there no one here?

327
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:17,033
- Ma'am Astrid...
- Where are

328
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:18,300
- Mookie and Olive?
- Ma'am, Ma'am!

329
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:21,033
Ma'am Olive brought
Mookie to the hospital.

330
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,700
Her leg is going
to be amputated.

331
00:22:23,767 --> 00:22:24,767
What?

332
00:22:26,967 --> 00:22:29,033
Just count to 10, okay?
